Commands for managing MCPAccessGrant and MCPAgentSession resources that feed the gateway policy layer.

With mcp-runtime auth login, commands use the platform API by default. Use --use-kube
to target the cluster with kubectl and a kubeconfig (cluster admin path).

Usage:
  mcp-runtime access [command]

Available Commands:
  grant       Manage MCPAccessGrant resources
  session     Manage MCPAgentSession resources

Flags:
  -h, --help       help for access
      --use-kube   Use kubectl and local kubeconfig instead of the platform API for supported commands

Global Flags:
      --debug   Enable debug mode with structured error logging

Use "mcp-runtime access [command] --help" for more information about a command.
